## Implementation patterns

- Use app/server/clients/prismaClient.ts for DB access
- Wrap via withErrorHandler / handleApiError; normalize Plaid errors with plaidApiError.ts
- Validate requests with Zod (app/schema/zod.ts) when applicable
- Use server/middleware/auth.ts globally and requireAdmin.ts for admin routes
- For long-running work, enqueue a BullMQ job (server/queues/*) and return early

## Adding an endpoint safely

- Create handler under app/server/api/<feature>/<name>.<method>.ts
- Parse/validate input and enforce access early
- Delegate to services; keep handler orchestration-focused
- Add tests under app/server/api/__tests__ covering success and failure
- If needed, expose a composable or store action to consume it from the client
